description:
This is a 9 minute workout called 'Hydrow Games: Race Day with James' from the channel James Dietz.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Advanced fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Competitor and The Adrenaline Rush vibe.
The The Competitor vibe means Gamified, leaderboard-driven, full-send energy. This is especially good for Those who need to chase a score or beat their own record. The The Adrenaline Rush vibe means Heart-racing, full-body intensity, unpredictable challenges. This is especially good for Those who crave challenge, variety, and adrenaline..
The technique difficulty is Intermediate and Advanced.
The effort required is Challenging and Extreme.

Original workout description: Challenge yourself in the third race of the Hydrow Games with James. This 7-minute drive is designed to push you to your limits and show what youâ€™re made of by mimicking the conditions of a 2,000-meter race. Start with a high intensity at 30 S/M, then settle into a powerful 28 S/M. James will guide you throughout the race to lean into discomfort, attack the race, and push your team on the leaderboard. Embrace the adrenaline, take it one stroke at a time, and bring out your best. Max rhythm: 34, Format: Intervals...
